        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I want prepend <br \/> to an form element. I use the following decorator:\r\n\r\nprotected $_elementDecorators = array(\r\n    'ViewHelper',\r\n    'Description',\r\n    'Errors',\r\n    array(array('LineBreak' => 'HtmlTag'), array('tag' => 'br', 'placement' => 'prepend')),\r\n    'Label',\r\n     array('HtmlTag', array('tag' => 'div', 'class' => 'zend_element')),\r\n);\r\n\r\nThe result of the LineBreak decoration is \"<br><\/br>\", but with options like \"openOnly\" it is invalid XHTML. It seems where is no way to place an empty tag like <br \/> with help of the standard decorators to the form.\r\n\r\n"
        },
