        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44073",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag does not appear to support these types of tags.\r\n\r\nThe decorator allows for openOnly and closeOnly but not for tags that require \/> at the end.  This would also be the case for <hr \/>.\r\n\r\nSince there are only a small number of tags that are affected by this (<br \/>, <hr \/>, others?) then I propose that the Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag is adapted to recognise these tags and render them as <tag \/>. Note: <input \/> tags will not be handled by Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag as they have their own classes.\r\n\r\nThe alternative would be to add another optional argument to Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag, 'singleTag', which would render the tag with \/> at the end.\r\n\r\nI would like to work on this issue but I think we need some additional input before I start as to which of the above resolutions would be best.\r\n\r\nG",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-20T05:33:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-20T05:33:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44075",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "*@Andreas*\r\nPlease use always the code tags and show us the desired output.\r\n\r\nHere is a workaround: (very simple with PHP 5.3)\r\n{code:title=Workaround PHP 5.3}\r\nprotected $_elementDecorators = array(\r\n    'ViewHelper',\r\n    'Description',\r\n    'Errors',\r\n    array(\r\n        \/\/ Decorator name\r\n        'Callback',\r\n        \/\/ Options\r\n        array(\r\n            'callback' => function($content, $element, array $options)\r\n            {\r\n                return '<br \/>';\r\n            },\r\n            'placement' => 'prepend',\r\n        )\r\n    ),\r\n    'Label',\r\n    array(\r\n        \/\/ Decorator name\r\n        'HtmlTag',\r\n        \/\/ Options\r\n        array(\r\n            'tag' => 'div',\r\n            'class' => 'zend_element',\r\n        ),\r\n    ),\r\n);\r\n{code}\r\n\"Callback\" is a standard decorator!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-20T06:37:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-20T06:39:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44144",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Have added a patch.\r\n\r\nA new option is available, 'selfClosing'.  This option requires a placement to be set as you cannot have content within a self closing tag.  Throws a Zend_Form_Decorator_Exception if no placement set.\r\n\r\nGuy",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-23T13:03:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-23T13:03:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44153",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is a bad idea:\r\n{code:title=Patch}\r\nprotected function _getSelfClosingTag($tag, array $attribs = null)\r\n{\r\n    \/\/ ...\r\n    $html .= ' \/>';\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nXHTML vs. HTML!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-24T05:25:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-24T05:25:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44159",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What would you suggest as a solution? Shouldnt the framework be XHTML compliant?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-24T05:42:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-24T05:42:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44161",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Both: HTML and XHTML!\r\n\r\n{code:title=Fix - not tested!}\r\n$element = $this->getElement();\r\n$view    = $element->getView();\r\n\r\n\/\/ XHTML or HTML end tag?\r\n$endTag = ' \/>';\r\nif (($view instanceof Zend_View_Abstract) && !$view->doctype()->isXhtml()) {\r\n    $endTag= '>';\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-24T05:52:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-24T05:52:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44162",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok, will amend code and tests and resubmit the patch.  G",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-24T05:58:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-24T05:58:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44195",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have updated the patch to differentiate between HTML and XHTML.  I have also split the patch into two files (tests and library).\r\n\r\nPlease could someone review the patches.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nG",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guyht",
                        "name": "guyht",
                        "displayName": "Guy Halford-Thompson",
                        "active": true
